title: Prep Profile: Lauren Wirtz, Fond du Lac
text:
Prep Profile: Lauren Wirtz, Fond du Lac Sam Oleson , Action Reporter Media 3:13 p.m. CDT October 12, 2015 Fond du Lac's Lauren Wirtz talks about the 2015 season. Fond du Lac’s Lauren Wirtz has been a solid contributor for the Cardinals in the back row this season. (Photo: Sam Oleson/Action Reporter Media) 2 CONNECT 5 TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Fond du Lac, Senior, Girls Volleyball 
Sports Lauren competes in 
Volleyball and softball 
Lauren’s week 
The senior libero recorded nine digs in the Cardinals’ 3-1 win over Appleton West last Tuesday and followed that up with 12 digs in a loss to Hortonville on Thursday. Wirtz then led Fond du Lac with 50 digs on Saturday as the Cardinals went 4-1 at an invitational hosted by Lodi. 
All-time team sports achievement 
Advancing to a national tournament as part of the Fondy Fusion softball team in the summer of 2014. 
No. 1 athletic goal 
Qualifying for the WIAA state girls volleyball tournament. 
Lauren’s thoughts 
“I’m supportive and I help my team when we’re down. I’m someone (teammates) can always come to if they have problems on or off the court. I try my hardest in every game.” 
Coach Kevin Santry’s thoughts 
“Lauren plays with fire. She plays aggressive defense and that’s one thing that we’ve been preaching about. She’s playing hard. She’s a leader on the court and off the court. She’s not a captain, but she’s filling the role of leader back there as a libero should.” 
Lauren’s favorites 
•Pro/college athlete: University of Wisconsin women’s volleyball player Lauren Carlini 
•Pro/college team: University of Wisconsin women’s volleyball team 
•Musical artist: Twenty One Pilots 
•Song of all time: “We Are Done” by The Madden Brothers 
•TV show: “Criminal Minds”
